This paper deals with information inequalities and their applications in network coding, which are topics that fall under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the use of auxiliary variables and the study of entropy space, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the Vamos network, which is a specific type of network, and thus falls under the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper presents several infinite families of inequalities, which could be relevant to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
